{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff44e-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2441"},"text":"§ 2441.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" War crimes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff44f-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Offense","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Whoever, whether inside or outside the United States, commits a war crime, in any of the circumstances described in subsection (b), shall be fined under this title or imprisoned for life or any term of years, or both, and if death results to the victim, shall also be subject to the penalty of death.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff450-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Jurisdiction","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"There is jurisdiction over an offense described in subsection (a) if—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff451-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the offense occurs in whole or in part within the United States; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff452-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" regardless of where the offense occurs—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff453-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/b/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" the victim or offender is—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff454-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/b/2/A/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a national of the United States or an alien lawfully admitted for permanent residence; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff455-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/b/2/A/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a member of the Armed Forces of the United States, regardless of nationality; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff456-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/b/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the offender is present in the United States, regardless of the nationality of the victim or offender.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff457-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definition","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"As used in this section the term “war crime” means any conduct—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff458-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" defined as a grave breach in any of the international conventions signed at Geneva 12 August 1949, or any protocol to such convention to which the United States is a party;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff459-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" prohibited by Article 23, 25, 27, or 28 of the Annex to the Hague Convention IV, Respecting the Laws and Customs of War on Land, signed 18 October 1907;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff45a-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/c/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" which constitutes a grave breach of common Article 3 (as defined in subsection (d)) when committed in the context of and in association with an armed conflict not of an international character; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff45b-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/c/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" of a person who, in relation to an armed conflict and contrary to the provisions of the Protocol on Prohibitions or Restrictions on the Use of Mines, Booby-Traps and Other Devices as amended at Geneva on 3 May 1996 (Protocol II as amended on 3 May 1996), when the United States is a party to such Protocol, willfully kills or causes serious injury to civilians.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff45c-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Common Article","children":[],"tail":" 3 "},{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Violations.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff45d-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Prohibited conduct","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c)(3), the term “grave breach of common Article 3” means any conduct (such conduct constituting a grave breach of common Article 3 of the international conventions done at Geneva ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-08-12"},"text":"August 12, 1949","children":[],"tail":"), as follows:"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff45e-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Torture","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The act of a person who commits, or conspires or attempts to commit, an act specifically intended to inflict severe physical or mental pain or suffering (other than pain or suffering incidental to lawful sanctions) upon another person within his custody or physical control for the purpose of obtaining information or a confession, punishment, intimidation, coercion, or any reason based on discrimination of any kind.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff45f-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Cruel or inhuman treatment","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The act of a person who commits, or conspires or attempts to commit, an act intended to inflict severe or serious physical or mental pain or suffering (other than pain or suffering incidental to lawful sanctions), including serious physical abuse, upon another within his custody or control.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff460-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Performing biological experiments","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The act of a person who subjects, or conspires or attempts to subject, one or more persons within his custody or physical control to biological experiments without a legitimate medical or dental purpose and in so doing endangers the body or health of such person or persons.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff461-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/1/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Murder","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The act of a person who intentionally kills, or conspires or attempts to kill, or kills whether intentionally or unintentionally in the course of committing any other offense under this subsection, one or more persons taking no active part in the hostilities, including those placed out of combat by sickness, wounds, detention, or any other cause.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff462-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/1/E"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"E"},"text":"(E)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Mutilation or maiming","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The act of a person who intentionally injures, or conspires or attempts to injure, or injures whether intentionally or unintentionally in the course of committing any other offense under this subsection, one or more persons taking no active part in the hostilities, including those placed out of combat by sickness, wounds, detention, or any other cause, by disfiguring the person or persons by any mutilation thereof or by permanently disabling any member, limb, or organ of his body, without any legitimate medical or dental purpose.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff463-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/1/F"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"F"},"text":"(F)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Intentionally causing serious bodily injury","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The act of a person who intentionally causes, or conspires or attempts to cause, serious bodily injury to one or more persons, including lawful combatants, in violation of the law of war.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff464-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/1/G"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"G"},"text":"(G)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Rape","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The act of a person who forcibly or with coercion or threat of force wrongfully invades, or conspires or attempts to invade, the body of a person by penetrating, however slightly, the anal or genital opening of the victim with any part of the body of the accused, or with any foreign object.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff465-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/1/H"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"H"},"text":"(H)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Sexual assault or abuse","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The act of a person who forcibly or with coercion or threat of force engages, or conspires or attempts to engage, in sexual contact with one or more persons, or causes, or conspires or attempts to cause, one or more persons to engage in sexual contact.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff466-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/1/I"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"I"},"text":"(I)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Taking hostages","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The act of a person who, having knowingly seized or detained one or more persons, threatens to kill, injure, or continue to detain such person or persons with the intent of compelling any nation, person other than the hostage, or group of persons to act or refrain from acting as an explicit or implicit condition for the safety or release of such person or persons.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff467-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definitions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of an offense under subsection (a) by reason of subsection (c)(3)—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff468-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the term “severe mental pain or suffering” shall be applied for purposes of paragraphs (1)(A) and (1)(B) in accordance with the meaning given that term in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s2340/2"},"text":"section 2340(2) of this title","children":[],"tail":";"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff469-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the term “serious bodily injury” shall be applied for purposes of paragraph (1)(F) in accordance with the meaning given that term in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s113/b/2"},"text":"section 113(b)(2) of this title","children":[],"tail":";"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff46a-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the term “sexual contact” shall be applied for purposes of paragraph (1)(G) in accordance with the meaning given that term in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s2246/3"},"text":"section 2246(3) of this title","children":[],"tail":";"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff46b-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/2/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" the term “serious physical pain or suffering” shall be applied for purposes of paragraph (1)(B) as meaning bodily injury that involves—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff46c-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/2/D/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a substantial risk of death;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff46d-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/2/D/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" extreme physical pain;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff46e-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/2/D/iii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iii"},"text":"(iii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a burn or physical disfigurement of a serious nature (other than cuts, abrasions, or bruises); or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff46f-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/2/D/iv"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iv"},"text":"(iv)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" significant loss or impairment of the function of a bodily member, organ, or mental faculty; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff470-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/2/E"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"E"},"text":"(E)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" the term “serious mental pain or suffering” shall be applied for purposes of paragraph (1)(B) in accordance with the meaning given the term “severe mental pain or suffering” (as defined in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s2340/2"},"text":"section 2340(2) of this title","children":[],"tail":"), except that—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff471-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/2/E/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the term “serious” shall replace the term “severe” where it appears; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff472-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/2/E/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" as to conduct occurring after the date of the enactment of the Military Commissions Act of 2006, the term “serious and non-transitory mental harm (which need not be prolonged)” shall replace the term “prolonged mental harm” where it appears.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff473-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Inapplicability of certain provisions with respect to collateral damage or incident of lawful attack","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The intent specified for the conduct stated in subparagraphs (D), (E), and (F) or paragraph (1) precludes the applicability of those subparagraphs to an offense under subsection (a) by reasons of subsection (c)(3) with respect to—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff474-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" collateral damage; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff475-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" death, damage, or injury incident to a lawful attack.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff476-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Inapplicability of taking hostages to prisoner exchange","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Paragraph (1)(I) does not apply to an offense under subsection (a) by reason of subsection (c)(3) in the case of a prisoner exchange during wartime.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff477-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/d/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definition of grave breaches","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The definitions in this subsection are intended only to define the grave breaches of common Article 3 and not the full scope of United States obligations under that Article.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff478-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Nonapplicability of Certain Limitations","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of an offense described in subsection (a) and further described in subsections (c)(1) and (c)(3), an indictment may be found or an information may be instituted at any time without limitation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff479-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Certification Requirement.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff47a-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/f/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In general","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"No prosecution for an offense described in subsection (a) shall be undertaken by the United States except on written certification of the Attorney General, the Deputy Attorney General, or an Assistant Attorney General, which function of approving prosecutions may not be delegated, that a prosecution by the United States is in the public interest and necessary to secure substantial justice.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff47b-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/f/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Offender present in united states","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For an offense for which jurisdiction exists under subsection (b)(2)(B) (and does not exist under any other provision of subsection (b)), the written certification required under paragraph (1) of this subsection that a prosecution by the United States is in the public interest and necessary to secure substantial justice shall be made by the Attorney General or the Deputy Attorney General, which function may not be delegated. In issuing such certification, the same official shall weigh and consider, among other relevant factors—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff47c-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/f/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" whether the alleged offender can be removed from the United States for purposes of prosecution in another jurisdiction; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff47d-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/f/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" potential adverse consequences for nationals, servicemembers, or employees of the United States.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff47e-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/g"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"g"},"text":"(g)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Input From Other Agency Heads","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of Defense and Secretary of State may submit to the Attorney General for consideration their views generally regarding potential benefits, or potential adverse consequences for nationals, servicemembers, or employees of the United States, of prosecutions of offenses for which jurisdiction exists under subsection (b)(2)(B).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff47f-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/h"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"h"},"text":"(h)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"No Judicial Review","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Certifications under subsection (f) and input from other agency heads under subsection (g) are not subject to judicial review.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff480-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Rules of Construction","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Nothing in this section shall be construed as—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff481-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/i/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" support for ratification of or accession to the Rome Statute of the International Criminal Court, which entered into force on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 2002","children":[],"tail":"; or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff482-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2441/i/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" consent by the United States to any assertion or exercise of jurisdiction by any international, hybrid, or foreign court.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb96ff483-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/192/s2/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–192, § 2(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-08-21"},"text":"Aug. 21, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/2104"},"text":"110 Stat. 2104","children":[],"tail":", § 2401; renumbered § 2441, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/294/tVI/s605/p/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–294, title VI, § 605(p)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-10-11"},"text":"Oct. 11, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/3510"},"text":"110 Stat. 3510","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/118/tV/s583"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–118, title V, § 583","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-11-26"},"text":"Nov. 26, 1997","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/111/2436"},"text":"111 Stat. 2436","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/dB/tIV/s4002/e/7"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, div. B, title IV, § 4002(e)(7)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-02"},"text":"Nov. 2, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1810"},"text":"116 Stat. 1810","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/366/s6/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–366, § 6(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/2633"},"text":"120 Stat. 2633","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/351/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–351, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2023-01-05"},"text":"Jan. 5, 2023","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/6265"},"text":"136 Stat. 6265","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb96ff484-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb96ff485-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idb96ff486-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The date of the enactment of the Military Commissions Act of 2006, referred to in subsec. (d)(2)(E)(ii), is the date of enactment of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/366"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–366","children":[],"tail":", which was approved "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 2006","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb96ff487-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2023—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/351/s2/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–351, § 2(1)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (b) and struck out former subsec. (b). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The circumstances referred to in subsection (a) are that the person committing such war crime or the victim of such war crime is a member of the Armed Forces of the United States or a national of the United States (as defined in section 101 of the Immigration and Nationality Act).”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (e) to (i). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/351/s2/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–351, § 2(2)","children":[],"tail":", added subsecs. (e) to (i)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—Subsec. (c)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/366/s6/b/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–366, § 6(b)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (3) and struck out former par. (3) which read as follows: “which constitutes a violation of common Article 3 of the international conventions signed at Geneva, 12 August 1949, or any protocol to such convention to which the United States is a party and which deals with non-international armed conflict; or”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/366/s6/b/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–366, § 6(b)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (d)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—Subsecs. (a) to (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273","children":[],"tail":" made technical correction to directory language of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/118/s583"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–118, § 583","children":[],"tail":". See 1997 Amendment notes below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1997—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/118/s583/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–118, § 583(1)","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273","children":[],"tail":", substituted “war crime” for “grave breach of the Geneva Conventions”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/118/s583/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–118, § 583(2)","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273","children":[],"tail":", substituted “war crime” for “breach” in two places."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/118/s583/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–118, § 583(3)","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273","children":[],"tail":", amended subsec. (c) generally. Prior to amendment, subsec. (c) read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(c) ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definitions","children":[],"tail":".—As used in this section, the term ‘grave breach of the Geneva Conventions’ means conduct defined as a grave breach in any of the international conventions relating to the laws of warfare signed at Geneva 12 August 1949 or any protocol to any such convention, to which the United States is a party.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/294"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–294","children":[],"tail":" renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s2401"},"text":"section 2401 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb96ff488-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb96ff489-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2006 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/366/s6/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–366, § 6(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/2635"},"text":"120 Stat. 2635","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/109/366/s6/b/2"},"text":"“The amendments made by this subsection [amending this section], except as specified in subsection (d)(2)(E) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s2441"},"text":"section 2441 of title 18","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, shall take effect as of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-11-26"},"text":"November 26, 1997","children":[],"tail":", as if enacted immediately after the amendments made by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/118/s583"},"text":"section 583 of Public Law 105–118","children":[],"tail":" [amending this section] (as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/s4002/e/7"},"text":"section 4002(e)(7) of Public Law 107–273","children":[],"tail":").”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb96ff48a-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2002 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/dB/tIV/s4002/e/7"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, div. B, title IV, § 4002(e)(7)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-02"},"text":"Nov. 2, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1810"},"text":"116 Stat. 1810","children":[],"tail":", provided that the amendment made by section 4002(e)(7) is effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-11-26"},"text":"Nov. 26, 1997","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitle","id":"idb96ff48b-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/192/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–192, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-08-21"},"text":"Aug. 21, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/2104"},"text":"110 Stat. 2104","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/104/192/s1"},"text":"“This Act [enacting this chapter] may be cited as the ‘War Crimes Act of 1996’.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idb96ff48c-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Implementation of Treaty Obligations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/366/s6/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–366, § 6(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/2632"},"text":"120 Stat. 2632","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/109/366/s6/a"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In general","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The acts enumerated in subsection (d) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s2441"},"text":"section 2441 of title 18","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, as added by subsection (b) of this section, and in subsection (c) of this section [enacting "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s2000dd–0"},"text":"section 2000dd–0 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare], constitute violations of common Article 3 of the Geneva Conventions prohibited by United States law."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Prohibition on grave breaches","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The provisions of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s2441"},"text":"section 2441 of title 18","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, as amended by this section, fully satisfy the obligation under Article 129 of the Third Geneva Convention for the United States to provide effective penal sanctions for grave breaches which are encompassed in common Article 3 in the context of an armed conflict not of an international character. No foreign or international source of law shall supply a basis for a rule of decision in the courts of the United States in interpreting the prohibitions enumerated in subsection (d) of such section 2441."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"“(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Interpretation by the president.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"“(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" As provided by the Constitution and by this section, the President has the authority for the United States to interpret the meaning and application of the Geneva Conventions and to promulgate higher standards and administrative regulations for violations of treaty obligations which are not grave breaches of the Geneva Conventions.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"“(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The President shall issue interpretations described by subparagraph (A) by Executive Order published in the Federal Register.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"“(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Any Executive Order published under this paragraph shall be authoritative (except as to grave breaches of common Article 3) as a matter of United States law, in the same manner as other administrative regulations.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"“(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Nothing in this section shall be construed to affect the constitutional functions and responsibilities of Congress and the judicial branch of the United States.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"“(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definitions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this subsection:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"“(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Geneva conventions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The term ‘Geneva Conventions’ means—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"“(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Convention for the Amelioration of the Condition of the Wounded and Sick in Armed Forces in the Field, done at Geneva ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-08-12"},"text":"August 12, 1949","children":[],"tail":" (6 UST 3217);"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"“(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Convention for the Amelioration of the Condition of the Wounded, Sick, and Shipwrecked Members of the Armed Forces at Sea, done at Geneva ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-08-12"},"text":"August 12, 1949","children":[],"tail":" (6 UST 3217);"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iii"},"text":"“(iii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Convention Relative to the Treatment of Prisoners of War, done at Geneva ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-08-12"},"text":"August 12, 1949","children":[],"tail":" (6 UST 3316); and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iv"},"text":"“(iv)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Convention Relative to the Protection of Civilian Persons in Time of War, done at Geneva ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-08-12"},"text":"August 12, 1949","children":[],"tail":" (6 UST 3516)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"“(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Third geneva convention","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The term ‘Third Geneva Convention’ means the international convention referred to in subparagraph (A)(iii).”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"idb96ff48d-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"executiveOrder","id":"idb96ff48e-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Order No. 13440","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Ex. Ord. No. 13440, ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-07-20"},"text":"July 20, 2007","children":[],"tail":", 72 F.R. 40707, which interpreted the Geneva Conventions Common Article 3 as applied to a program of detention and interrogation operated by the Central Intelligence Agency, was revoked by Ex. Ord. No. 13491, § 1, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-01-22"},"text":"Jan. 22, 2009","children":[],"tail":", 74 F.R. 4893, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s2000dd"},"text":"section 2000dd of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
